      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i am working on my psych dissertation and im stuck on a result. i have a p-value of 0.06 for one of my main hypotheses. theoretically it looks like there is a trend, but my advisor is saying it is not statistically significant. can u explain why that is? like why can't we just call it significant if it's that close?",
