      "role": "user",
      "content": "right, so the noise basically hides the actual effect. it's like the data is being obscured by random stuff. can u explain more about what actually constitutes that \"noise\"? like, is it just math errors or is it something more systemic in how data is collected? i'm trying to write this section on why a trend might be lost in the shuffle.",
